    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1469779801" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1469779801" />
    <a title="Sophia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5063928-sophia"><img alt="Sophia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1432187496p2/5063928.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1469779801?book_show_action=true">Dec 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sophia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sophia" href="/user/show/5063928-sophia">Sophia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781408411506" href="/book/show/8196712-the-reluctant-widow">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5063928-sophia?shelf=audio-books">audio-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5063928-sophia?shelf=historical-romance">historical-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1469779801" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17094465767240661130">This was my second time through this story and I have to say this author&apos;s work stands the test of time and re-reading. I appreciated it more than I did in the first place.<br/><br/>I saw more humor and wit than I did the first time around. I saw the subtle hints of romance where I didn&apos;t see the evidence of it before and I was most struck by one of the more dubious characters in the story, Frances Cheviot.<br/><br/>The story is most definitely old school Regency Romance at its best with a tinge of the Gothic to it</span>
  <span id="freeText17094465767240661130" style="display:none">This was my second time through this story and I have to say this author's work stands the test of time and re-reading. I appreciated it more than I did in the first place.<br /><br />I saw more humor and wit than I did the first time around. I saw the subtle hints of romance where I didn't see the evidence of it before and I was most struck by one of the more dubious characters in the story, Frances Cheviot.<br /><br />The story is most definitely old school Regency Romance at its best with a tinge of the Gothic to it. I wasn't that into the heroine the first time around, but found her more than tolerable this time. She has a stinging tongue, but I could see how the hero's laid back cool attitude in the face of the mayhem going on would drive her to it. They are quite the pair and I enjoyed their sparring.<br /><br />The narrator did a fantastic job capturing the tone, pacing, and characters.<br /><br />In summation, I was delighted by this re-read in the form of an audio version.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17094465767240661130" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1469779801">
