<div id="review_293085314" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/293085314" />
    <a title="Lady Wesley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6730840-lady-wesley"><img alt="Lady Wesley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1380306898p2/6730840.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/293085314?book_show_action=true">Mar 12, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lady Wesley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lady Wesley" href="/user/show/6730840-lady-wesley">Lady Wesley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781408411506" href="/book/show/8196712-the-reluctant-widow">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6730840-lady-wesley?shelf=listened">listened</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer293085314" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11187781518919898337"><i>Review of the audiobook</i><br/><br/>I read this book years ago and thought it was just fine. Since then I have read almost all of Georgette Heyer&apos;s romances and mysteries, so I thought to give this one another try. I liked it more than before. I think that when I first began reading Heyer I was expecting more romance in her Regency romances. Now, I have come to appreciate her books for what they are: beautifully written comedies of manners with a bit of adventure and a very chaste romance. <br/><br/>This one is rather</span>
  <span id="freeText11187781518919898337" style="display:none"><i>Review of the audiobook</i><br /><br />I read this book years ago and thought it was just fine. Since then I have read almost all of Georgette Heyer's romances and mysteries, so I thought to give this one another try. I liked it more than before. I think that when I first began reading Heyer I was expecting more romance in her Regency romances. Now, I have come to appreciate her books for what they are: beautifully written comedies of manners with a bit of adventure and a very chaste romance. <br /><br />This one is rather short, quite funny, and flows along nicely. Of course, it has the trademark abrupt ending, which still annoys me. But at least, I'm not surprised any more.<br /><br />Cornelius Garrett does an excellent job narrating.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11187781518919898337" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

